##  Project Overview

This project is a **production-ready RESTful API** built for task management with robust authentication, role-based access control, and secure data handling. 

## Task Manager App

A full-stack task management system with secure user authentication, role-based access control, scalable backend APIs, and an interactive frontend for API testing.

```
 ##API Documentation
Postman Collection included:
 backend\src\API_documentation.postman_collection.json

Import into Postman to test all endpoints.

https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/46592324/2sBXVcjs2x


```



##  Features Implemented

###  Authentication & Authorization
- User registration with password hashing (bcrypt)
-  JWT-based authentication with HTTP-only cookies
-  Secure login/logout functionality
-  Role-based access control (User vs Admin)
-  Protected routes with middleware

###  CRUD Operations (Task Entity)
-  Create tasks (authenticated users)
-  Read tasks (user-specific & filtered)
-  Update tasks (with validation)
-  Delete tasks (owner/admin only)

###  Security & Validation
-  Password hashing with bcrypt (10 rounds)
-  JWT token with 1-hour expiration
-  HTTP-only cookies for XSS protection
-  Input validation using express-validator
-  Centralized error handling
-  Email normalization (lowercase)

### Documentation & Best Practices
-  Comprehensive Postman collection
-  RESTful API design principles
-  Proper HTTP status codes
-  Modular project structure
-  MVC architecture pattern
-  Environment-based configuration

---

##  Tech Stack

| Category | Technology |
|----------|-----------|
| **Runtime** | Node.js (v18+) |
| **Framework** | Express.js 5.x |
| **Database** | MongoDB (Mongoose ODM) |
| **Authentication** | JWT + bcrypt |
| **Validation** | express-validator |
| **Security** | cookie-parser, CORS |
| **Development** | nodemon, dotenv |

---
 ##Security Measures

| Feature          | Description                 |
| ---------------- | --------------------------- |
| Password Hashing | bcrypt (10 rounds)          |
| Token Security   | JWT + HTTP-only cookies     |
| Token Expiry     | 1 hour                      |
| XSS Protection   | Cookie flags & sanitization |
| Validation       | express-validator           |
| Error Handling   | Centralized middleware      |



 Project Structure

├── backend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── controllers/       # Business logic
│   │   ├── routes/            # API endpoints (/api/v1)
│   │   ├── models/            # Database schemas
│   │   ├── middleware/        # Auth & role checks
│   │   └── config/            # DB & server config
│   ├── .env.example
│   └── package.json
│
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── pages/             # Auth, Dashboard, Task Pages
│   │   ├── components/        # UI Components
│   │   ├── context/           # AuthContext (JWT)
│   │   └── services/          # API handlers (Axios)
│   └── package.json
│
└── README.md


## Installation & Setup
Backend Setup
cd backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env
npm run dev          # Starts server on http://localhost:5000

Environment Variables

.env

PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/task_manager
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key_here
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

Frontend Setup
cd frontend
npm install
npm start             # Runs on http://localhost:3000


If required, update API base URL in src/services/api.js.


